<DocsLayout title="Quick Start" description="Get PicFast running in minutes.">
  <h1>Quick Start</h1>
  <p>
    PicFast is a self-hosted image hosting service. It takes less than 5 minutes to get running.
  </p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Docker</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.postgresql.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PostgreSQL</a> 16+ (or use the included Docker Compose setup)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>1. Start with Docker Compose</h2>
  <p>Create a <code>docker-compose.yml</code> file:</p>
  <pre><code>version: '3.8'
services:
  picfast:
    image: picfast/picfast:latest
    ports:
      - "8080:8080"
    volumes:
      - ./data:/data
    environment:
      - PICFAST_DATABASE_URL=postgres://picfast:picfast@postgres:5432/picfast?sslmode=disable
      - PICFAST_JWT_SECRET=your-secret-here
    depends_on:
      - postgres

  postgres:
    image: postgres:16-alpine
    environment:
      - POSTGRES_DB=picfast
      - POSTGRES_USER=picfast
      - POSTGRES_PASSWORD=picfast
    volumes:
      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data

volumes:
  pgdata:</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Configure</h2>
  <p>Copy the example config and edit it:</p>
  <pre><code>cp config.example.yaml config.yaml
$EDITOR config.yaml</code></pre>
  <p>Key settings to change:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>jwt.secret</code> — set a strong random secret</li>
    <li><code>server.base_url</code> — your public URL (e.g. <code>https://pics.yoursite.com</code>)</li>
    <li><code>app.admin_email</code> and <code>app.admin_password</code> — your admin account</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Run</h2>
  <pre><code>docker compose up -d</code></pre>
  <p>PicFast will automatically run database migrations on startup.</p>

  <h2>4. Verify</h2>
  <p>Open <code>http://localhost:8080</code> in your browser. You should see the login page.</p>
  <p>Log in with the admin credentials you set in <code>config.yaml</code>.</p>

